<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-03T15:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-03T15:32:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1267: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-03T16:00:00-04:32">July 3, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>71. The Bolivian Minister in Asuncion was given definite instructions on
                            Wednesday night to leave at once if Paraguayan reply was <pb facs="0858" n="744" xml:id="pg_744"/> unsatisfactory and the reply has been so
                            considered here. The Bolivian Foreign Minister stated last night that
                            the Minister would have to leave today if it were on foot but the
                            Foreign Office has at this date received no advices of his departure nor
                            has the Paraguayan Minister here received instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>